an class=title> Sky Raid, Sat/Sun, January 11-12</span><hr size=1> This is tentative atm (it *is* two months from now) but we decided to go ahead and reserve this weekend and just change it later if need be since everything up until then is booked solid. However, we have a lot of people that need epic drops and is something we need to do.<br>
<br>
Sky is not like Hate, it is not like Fear. It *requires* commitment for the full 2 days. Each island drops 24 keys to the next island(s), so at least for the first day we will only have 24 people, so need people that can stay the whole day, are 55+ especially, decently equipped, and on the ball. Sky is a two day raid and I imagine that we will possibly bring more groups in on day two to get more people experience in Sky and get enough people in to do some of the later isles. I know it may sound scary to some of you, but believe me, we have the firepower to do it, and assuming it goes through, two months from now we will be rocking even more =)<br>
<br>
You will need to bring the following on your toon....Food and Drink to survive several days, enough consumables to go the entire 2 days (peridots, etc), 20 peridots to contribute to your cleric to help alleviate their costs. <br>
<br>
You will need the following for yourself...A good cushion on your EQ chair, some snacks and soda on hand, and whatever else you may need to survive two 12+ hour raid days. Please try to arrange your life that you are free all day for both days. Essentially, we want to know who would like to come and could possibly schedule that weekend around this raid, and then when the time for the raid comes (during the week prior to it) get people nailed down and committing to coming. So if you would like to come, post your intent, and when we get closer to it, we will see who can actually come.<br>
<br>
All &quot;cash&quot; loot will be collected by myself and divided equally among the three guilds after the raid is completed. Major gem drops will also be split between the guilds and distributed afterward. Loot will be determined via the loot list as always, but there may be an alternate scheme as most of the loot is quest loot, and requires several drops, so this will be worked out and announced before hand as it doesn't make sense to have 10 people with 1 quest drop and no equipment per class.<br>
<br>
As I said, we need as many people to be level 55+ as possible. If you are lower that doesn't mean you can't come, but a level 46 melee is going to get low priority for the raid, because we need plenty of DPS, healing, and tanking to clear the mid to later islands. Also, you WILL die on this raid, be prepared for that. For 3-7 islands, it will take a couple of attempts (making sure to kill 1-3+ mobs per attempt) folloed by CRs in order to get the number of mobs on the islands down to a manageable size. There are long respawn times on the mobs (which is why only 24 will be there for day 1) so picking off a few mobs at a time followed by CR works well. We will try to have a necro available that can use stackable coffins to make CR easier and more painless on these attempts, one with enough essence emeralds to res a cleric as many times as needed.<br>
<br>
After we do this *once* and have the strategy down it will become much easier and funner.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of epic drops in Sky. If you want to be in line for them you need to be at the point where you will merit consideration. A ranger that has done nothing on their epic and is level 47 will not be too high in the queu for a stone. So make it a priority to level, and a priority to work on your epic. Remember, anyone can schedule an epic raid, you just need to do it with enough advance notice enough people will be available to come help. More information will be forthcoming in future weeks.<br>
<br>
This post will be on all the Alliance guild boards. Feel free to post any questions on any of these threads. <br>
